  "body": "I'm forking BSC Node through \r\n`npx hardhat node --fork https://bsc-dataseed1.binance.org --fork-block-number 26769200`\r\n\r\nMy script code is \r\n\r\n```\r\nasync function checkBalance() {\r\n    const provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(\"http://localhost:8545\");\r\n    const wbnbAddress = \"0xbb4CdB9CBd36B01bD1cBaEBF2De08d9173bc095c\";\r\n    const wbnbContract = await ethers.getContractAt(\"IERC20\", wbnbAddress);\r\n    const balance = await wbnbContract.balanceOf(\"0x32596E35eE58e46421585483e5463bc559A4037C\");\r\n    console.log(`WBNB balance: ${ethers.utils.formatEther(balance)} `);\r\n}\r\n\r\n\r\ncheckBalance();\r\n```\r\nIf i run it through it will give me an exact balance of wbnb \r\n`npx hardhat run scripts/bscbalance.js --network bsc`\r\n\r\n\r\nBut if i try to run it with the bsc fork it gives me an error of \r\n`Error: call revert exception [ See: https://links.ethers.org/v5-errors-CALL_EXCEPTION ] (method=\"balanceOf(address)\", data=\"0x\", errorArgs=null, errorName=null, errorSignature=null, reason=null, code=CALL_EXCEPTION, version=abi/5.7.0)`\r\n\r\nAny advice on this?\r\n\r\n",
