    "body": "> But if i try to run it with the bsc fork it gives me an error of\r\n\r\nHow are you doing that, exactly?\r\n\r\nJust in case, I think this is usually an error:\r\n\r\n> const provider = new ethers.providers.JsonRpcProvider(\"http://localhost:8545\");\r\n\r\nYou should use `hre.ethers.provider` instead. That provider will be connected to the network you chose. So, when you are using `--network bsc`, it will connect to BSC, and when you don't specify a network it will use the Hardhat network by default.",
